{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"mcp_tool_call","server":"remem","tool":"get_observations","arguments":{"ids":[79301],"source":"memory","project":"remem"},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"[\n  {\n    \"branch\": \"main\",\n    \"created_at_epoch\": 1781792297,\n    \"files\": \"[\\\"src/api/handlers/candidates.rs\\\",\\\"src/api/handlers/detail.rs\\\",\\\"src/api/handlers/graph.rs\\\",\\\"src/api/handlers/list.rs\\\",\\\"src/api/tests.rs\\\",\\\"src/api/tests/web_regressions.rs\\\",\\\"src/api/types.rs\\\",\\\"src/mcp/server/runtime.rs\\\",\\\"src/doctor/mcp_processes.rs\\\",\\\"src/install/duplicates.rs\\\",\\\"src/install/runtime.rs\\\"]\",\n    \"id\": 79301,\n    \"memory_type\": \"bugfix\",\n    \"project\": \"remem\",\n    \"scope\": \"project\",\n    \"session_id\": null,\n    \"status\": \"active\",\n    \"text\": \"On 2026-06-18, the remem GitHub queue was handled with threads/no-merge policy. Root worktree was dirty/stale, so isolated worktrees were used. Final remote state: PR #527 head 2317fbc, #529 head ca20e46, #531 head 2b2939a; all three open PRs had CI SUCCESS, mergeStateStatus CLEAN, and no unresolved review threads. #527 fixes web read-only API review feedback: documented GET /api/v1/memories route, pending_review candidates, bidirectional detail edges, bounded/current graph fanout, current-memory stats/list filters, branchless branch filter, owner-aware project list filtering, project-filtered candidates, memory detail access tracking, and current-link graph nodes. #531 fixes issue #530 runtime drift: MCP startup DB preflight fail-fast with context, doctor stale MCP process warning with Unix gating, configured binary duplicate/version/schema drift checks including wrapper/bare-command handling, install restart/doctor guidance. #529 was already clean. Issues #526/#528/#530 remain open only because PRs are not merged. #390/#385 are externally blocked; #381/#383/#384 remain roadmap umbrellas. Important merge caveat: #527 and #531 both bump version files from the same base (0.5.94 vs 0.5.95), so after merging one, rebase/reconcile the other before merging.\",\n    \"title\": \"June 18 GitHub queue cleanup for PRs 527, 529, 531\",\n    \"topic_key\": \"github-queue-2026-06-18-pr527-pr531\",\n    \"updated_at_epoch\": 1781792297\n  }\n]"}],"structured_content":null},"error":null,"status":"completed"}}
